Package model

Class _CustDivCountryCombo

  • java.lang.Object
    • model._CustDivCountryCombo
  • public class _CustDivCountryCombo
extends java.lang.Object
    The _CustDivCountryCombo class holds a combination of Customer, Division, and Country objects and is used in the main form Customers Table and for sending data to customerModifyController.
    Version:
    1
    Author:
    Mary Williams

      • _CustDivCountryCombo

        public _CustDivCountryCombo​(Customer customer,
                            Division fld,
                            Country country)
        The constructor creates a combination class of Customer, Division, and Country, as well as setting variables to make it easier to put data into the Customers Table.
        Parameters:
        customer - The Customer object to be given to the Customer/Division/Country Combo.
        fld - The Division object to be given to the Customer/Division/Country Combo.
        country - The Country object to be given to the Customer/Division/Country Combo.
